comment: It is obvious that the United States continues to show how weak and corrupt it's justice system is by not charging this parasite with perjury within its own borders while the parasite continues to abuse and defame the man she has been PROVEN to have abused and defamed in the past. I hope with all my heart that Australia will at least show the world that "celebrities" (if you can call the parasite that) and WOMEN should be held accountable for their evil actions.
commentable_entity.title: Extradite Amber Heard to Australia
commentable_entity.description:
To the United States Secretary of State
Antony Blinken.

Amber Heard is being investigated by Australia's Department of Agriculture, Water and the Environment (DAWE) over allegations that she lied under oath after bringing her pet dogs into the country in May 2015. Because of Australia's strict quarantine laws, foreign pets must be quarantined for 10 days when first brought into the country. Government officials asked Heard at the time to remove the dogs from Australia or have them euthanized. The dogs were flown back to the United States, and in July 2015 Heard was charged with illegally importing them to Australia. Australia’s restrictions on importing dogs are just one part of a broader biosecurity policy that is notoriously strict. Australia's geographical distance from much of the rest of the world and its relatively late contact with the West means that its biological ecosystem is unlike those of many other nations. To protect this, the country restricts what can be brought into the country. The investigation has obtained plenty of evidence of Amber Heard’s wrong doing and proves she perjured her self when questioned by Australian authorities. She needs to be held accountable and we the United States have to show that we respect our allies and other countries laws no matter the the fame status of the US citizen that commits the crime. By not delivering Amber Heard to Australian Authorities we will be sending the message that the USA thinks our elite are above the laws of other countries.
commentable_entity.letter_body: United States Secretary of State Antony Blinken,
